description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: &lt;/strong&gt;15 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;Aerodrome House&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Southern Health NHS Foundation Trust (SHFT) have been working alongside local South East Hampshire MS societies to develop a role to support the provision of MS services locally and we are pleased to announce Southern Health NHS Foundation Trust is now looking to appoint an MS nurse. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post of MS Nurse will work in the provision of community based Multiple Sclerosis services across South East Hampshire. You will work closely to establish the workload and to support the team in providing an efficient, high quality service within these areas.   &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a member of our friendly and supportive team you will be working to support the delivery of multiple sclerosis service provision for patients within the community across Fareham, Gosport, Havant, Waterlooville, Petersfield and Hayling Island. The role also entails a high proportion of advice and training for patients alongside other Health and Social Care professionals within the region, acting as a source of specialist advice for local professionals. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The real focus of this role is to work within this busy team to provide education, specialist advice and assessment, which will lead to better individual outcomes and reduce admissions to hospital. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A keen interest in multiple sclerosis (MS) supported by experience of working with patients with MS/neurological conditions, as well as an MS qualification or a willingness to undertake this in the future is essential. Experience of teaching in any capacity would be essential and some experience of working within the primary care setting is preferred. In return for your skills this posts offers a real opportunity for further development in this field of work and as such, as an employer, we would provide regular supervision alongside a detailed, tailored training program (both internal and external) to ensure you have the necessary skills to support the service effectively. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The candidate will need to have excellent interpersonal and communication skills to enable them to work with multiple professional organisations and agencies, whilst having the ability to work autonomously and within a team. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information or for an informal discussion please contact Amy Harbour on 02392681067 in the first instance. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Happy to talk flexible working&lt;/strong&gt;-&lt;strong&gt; all requests for flexible and part time working will be considered.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Follow us on Facebook and on Twitter:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
